1
00:00:22,626 --> 00:00:25,780
I have no reason to go
unless it's a top performance at a top stage.

2
00:00:25,780 --> 00:00:29,717
Make that happen if you want me to go.

3
00:00:30,327 --> 00:00:33,664
Have you not gotten over it yet?

4
00:00:55,410 --> 00:00:57,918
Almighty Cha, it's okay.

5
00:00:57,918 --> 00:00:59,877
Just do what we did at the rehearsal.

6
00:00:59,877 --> 00:01:01,716
It's okay, Cha Yoo Jin!

7
00:02:29,085 --> 00:02:30,886
You were wrong.

8
00:02:32,221 --> 00:02:33,960
These are the friends

9
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:36,659
who made me feel like the best
when I wasn't the best.

10
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:40,182
You were wrong again.

11
00:02:41,130 --> 00:02:43,466
Showing my heart was not a weakness.

12
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:45,901
It returned with another heart.

13
00:03:43,751 --> 00:03:45,853
There are so many of them.

14
00:03:46,688 --> 00:03:49,251
You called me here
with an excuse of Seol Nae Il

15
00:03:49,251 --> 00:03:51,159
but the reason is Dr. Kim?

16
00:03:52,112 --> 00:03:55,548
I heard Cha Dong Woo came by
to see your concert yesterday.

17
00:03:57,690 --> 00:04:00,501
He'll flip
Sun Young's heart upside down again

18
00:04:00,501 --> 00:04:01,835
with your problem.

19
00:04:01,835 --> 00:04:04,460
He's been doing that all along.

20
00:04:04,460 --> 00:04:06,140
I'm sorry.

21
00:04:07,509 --> 00:04:10,092
It's been a while
since you went to Dr. Kim, right?

22
00:04:10,092 --> 00:04:12,547
Will you just waste time?

23
00:04:12,547 --> 00:04:13,918
Try as hard as you can,

24
00:04:13,918 --> 00:04:16,984
but when things don't work out,
you should learn to give up.

25
00:04:21,756 --> 00:04:25,526
Raise your left arm
as high as your shoulder.

26
00:04:26,188 --> 00:04:29,491
It should feel heavy
as if you're holding a dictionary.

27
00:04:30,498 --> 00:04:34,169
Now, we're going back
to when you were 10 years old.

28
00:04:34,169 --> 00:04:38,005
Cha Yoo Jin, you're on a plane.

29
00:04:38,742 --> 00:04:40,744
What happened?

30
00:04:51,505 --> 00:04:55,475
Gymnopedie. I like this music, too.

31
00:05:05,101 --> 00:05:07,835
This was when Sunbae was little, right?

32
00:05:07,835 --> 00:05:10,838
He looks exactly the same as now.

33
00:05:13,127 --> 00:05:17,376
But I guess he wasn't afraid of water then.

34
00:05:17,376 --> 00:05:21,918
Do you know about that?

35
00:05:21,918 --> 00:05:23,918
Pardon?

36
00:05:23,918 --> 00:05:25,918
I guess...

37
00:05:25,918 --> 00:05:28,910
Well, this is the first time
Yoo Jin brought his girlfriend.

38
00:05:29,737 --> 00:05:32,873
I didn't know he'd really bring you here
just because I told him.

39
00:05:33,751 --> 00:05:36,751
If you're that close,
I guess you should know.

40
00:05:36,751 --> 00:05:38,055
About what?

41
00:05:40,345 --> 00:05:42,046
About Yoo Jin's accident.

42
00:05:45,585 --> 00:05:48,127
The plane accident.

43
00:05:48,127 --> 00:05:49,537
Uncle!

44
00:05:52,058 --> 00:05:53,626
What are you doing right now?

45
00:06:11,678 --> 00:06:12,859
I...

46
00:06:14,918 --> 00:06:16,449
can't go study abroad.

47
00:06:18,084 --> 00:06:21,454
I can't get on a plane or a ship.

48
00:06:23,012 --> 00:06:25,127
Isn't it funny?

49
00:06:25,127 --> 00:06:26,793
You can mock me.

50
00:06:27,726 --> 00:06:29,294
Why?

51
00:06:31,537 --> 00:06:33,639
Trauma from the plane accident.

52
00:06:34,483 --> 00:06:38,219
I was dropped to the sea wearing a life vest.

53
00:06:39,225 --> 00:06:43,262
Since then, I can't get on a plane or a ship.

54
00:06:45,225 --> 00:06:48,661
Does that mean you can't go study abroad?

55
00:06:49,516 --> 00:06:52,626
It's not that you are not going.

56
00:06:52,626 --> 00:06:54,543
You can't go?

57
00:06:54,543 --> 00:06:57,390
You wanted to go study abroad.

58
00:07:00,508 --> 00:07:03,127
Why are you about to cry? I didn't even cry.

59
00:07:03,127 --> 00:07:05,565
I wasn't going to cry.

60
00:07:09,518 --> 00:07:11,753
Why would you cry over this?
It's no big deal.

61
00:07:25,552 --> 00:07:27,253
Bye.

62
00:07:31,024 --> 00:07:32,558
Sunbae.

63
00:07:33,375 --> 00:07:35,410
You don't just want to go home, do you?

64
00:08:09,128 --> 00:08:10,830
Gymnopedie.

65
00:08:12,539 --> 00:08:17,677
The music taught me
that simplicity can be plentiful.

66
00:08:18,137 --> 00:08:20,751
Is this from the composer's wish,

67
00:08:20,751 --> 00:08:24,577
for the audience
to soak to the music comfortably.

68
00:08:27,262 --> 00:08:30,798
You're working hard
to comfort me, Seol Nae Il.

69
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:46,857
Your event for me
was playing the piano for me?

70
00:08:51,751 --> 00:08:54,835
You like it when I play the piano.

71
00:08:54,835 --> 00:08:59,506
And I heard
your grandfather liked this music, too.

72
00:09:11,585 --> 00:09:15,054
It's Professor's watch.
When did you receive this?

73
00:09:16,289 --> 00:09:20,565
Before Milch was dragged to Germany.

74
00:09:20,565 --> 00:09:23,002
No wonder he was calling you "Baby, Baby".

75
00:09:23,002 --> 00:09:24,964
He really likes you.

76
00:09:25,529 --> 00:09:28,732
I like it
because it feels warmer than new ones.

77
00:09:29,783 --> 00:09:32,752
Have you tried hypnotherapy?

78
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,902
I tried everything.

79
00:09:37,078 --> 00:09:39,579
I heard it could last a lifetime...

80
00:09:39,579 --> 00:09:41,251
and it's true.

81
00:09:41,251 --> 00:09:44,173
I saw it on TV, too.

82
00:09:44,940 --> 00:09:46,918
Using this to induce hypnosis.

83
00:09:46,918 --> 00:09:48,710
It's about focus.

84
00:09:48,710 --> 00:09:50,523
Maybe it's a scam.

85
00:09:51,512 --> 00:09:55,960
When someone said,
"You're falling asleep, asleep,"

86
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:58,960
and they really fell asleep.

87
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:04,771
Yes, I heard hypnosis is easy
if the person trusts the partner.

88
00:10:06,293 --> 00:10:08,585
Maybe it's because I can't trust people?

89
00:10:08,585 --> 00:10:12,699
You are sleepy, you are sleepy.

90
00:10:17,164 --> 00:10:20,367
Sunbae, are you asleep?

91
00:10:22,002 --> 00:10:23,536
Sunbae.

92
00:10:25,464 --> 00:10:28,233
You didn't fall asleep for real, did you?

93
00:10:28,821 --> 00:10:31,123
Wake up.

94
00:10:36,416 --> 00:10:37,877
You were asleep.

95
00:10:37,877 --> 00:10:40,360
What do you mean?
I've been awake the whole time.

96
00:10:41,295 --> 00:10:42,796
I'm thirsty.

97
00:10:50,446 --> 00:10:52,324
Do I really have to get rid of this?

98
00:10:52,339 --> 00:10:54,675
What's so scary about this fan?

99
00:10:54,675 --> 00:10:57,377
You didn't know?
A lot of students are scared of it.

100
00:10:57,377 --> 00:11:00,835
They are all just lazy.

101
00:11:00,835 --> 00:11:04,017
This is the symbol of my education.

102
00:11:04,017 --> 00:11:08,355
I taught many students with this fan
and sent them off to competitions.

103
00:11:08,355 --> 00:11:11,158
Our school students are really nice.

104
00:11:11,158 --> 00:11:16,002
Even elementary students these days
upload a video of getting flicked

105
00:11:16,002 --> 00:11:18,169
and report the incident.

106
00:11:18,169 --> 00:11:19,684
What?

107
00:11:19,684 --> 00:11:21,002
How about this?

108
00:11:21,002 --> 00:11:23,835
We had a bet
over Cha Yoo Jin's duet performance, right?

109
00:11:23,835 --> 00:11:25,960
I haven't told you the condition
from that bet yet.

110
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:27,626
That was ages ago.

111
00:11:27,626 --> 00:11:29,776
I'll tell you now.

112
00:11:30,907 --> 00:11:33,626
Hide your fan for a while, please.

113
00:11:33,626 --> 00:11:36,917
She needs compliments more than the fan.

114
00:12:00,641 --> 00:12:02,609
What do I do?

115
00:12:09,109 --> 00:12:16,364
♪ I woke up this morning
and went to the bathroom ♪

116
00:12:17,701 --> 00:12:24,307
♪ If I push hard,
I'll get a good bowl movement ♪

117
00:12:34,050 --> 00:12:36,252
Would you like some cookies?

118
00:12:40,599 --> 00:12:44,703
I received the score yesterday.
I mean, the Fart Song.

119
00:12:45,482 --> 00:12:48,710
I was surprised. It has its charm.

120
00:12:48,710 --> 00:12:54,928
It flows with the player's emotions
and it has a good structure, too.

121
00:12:56,130 --> 00:12:59,200
How about completing the Fart Song with me?

122
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:00,867
The Fart Song?

123
00:13:03,334 --> 00:13:05,035
Can you come closer?

124
00:13:07,839 --> 00:13:09,540
One step.

125
00:13:11,295 --> 00:13:13,063
One step closer.

126
00:13:14,382 --> 00:13:16,584
See? I don't have the fan.

127
00:13:18,668 --> 00:13:22,376
I've wanted to tell you this for a long time.

128
00:13:22,376 --> 00:13:24,437
Yes?

129
00:13:29,476 --> 00:13:32,579
It's not the 'Fart' Song.
It's the 'Gas' Song.

130
00:13:34,275 --> 00:13:35,148
Gas?

131
00:13:35,148 --> 00:13:40,820
Fart' has a murky smell,
but 'Gas' has a cheerful smell.

132
00:13:43,623 --> 00:13:46,693
Fart or Gas, they both smell!

133
00:13:47,748 --> 00:13:51,835
I see. It is really a cheerful smell.

134
00:13:51,835 --> 00:13:58,671
Should we play the Fart...
I mean, the Gas Song?

135
00:13:59,906 --> 00:14:01,641
Here, have a seat.

136
00:14:32,919 --> 00:14:34,720
It's so hard.

137
00:14:54,982 --> 00:14:57,543
- You should give in this time.
- No.

138
00:14:57,543 --> 00:15:00,501
I've been giving in many times,
so you should give in this time.

139
00:15:00,501 --> 00:15:03,303
I said no!

140
00:15:06,172 --> 00:15:07,607
Mini Min Hee!

141
00:15:11,874 --> 00:15:15,293
Do they actually like you
or are they just competitive?

142
00:15:15,293 --> 00:15:18,118
They spend more time fighting with each other
than following you around.

143
00:15:18,118 --> 00:15:19,293
Make your decision soon.

144
00:15:19,293 --> 00:15:23,002
I don't like either of them.

145
00:15:23,002 --> 00:15:24,169
I already told them.

146
00:15:24,169 --> 00:15:26,293
And they're still like that?

147
00:15:26,293 --> 00:15:28,861
- No!
- You give in!

148
00:15:29,475 --> 00:15:31,460
Shouldn't we go and stop them?

149
00:15:31,460 --> 00:15:32,793
They're okay.

150
00:15:32,793 --> 00:15:35,635
I guess they just don't have anything to do.

151
00:15:58,504 --> 00:16:00,841
My Shi Won is wearing a skirt.

152
00:16:01,757 --> 00:16:04,460
Be careful when you're wearing a skirt.

153
00:16:04,460 --> 00:16:06,918
She's wearing it in a million years,
so what would she know?

154
00:16:06,918 --> 00:16:10,419
Be careful. You're ruining my eyes.

155
00:16:12,853 --> 00:16:16,223
I wouldn't be wearing this,
unless I'm seeing my grandpa.

156
00:16:22,090 --> 00:16:24,043
If you feel uncomfortable, cover with this.

157
00:16:24,043 --> 00:16:26,210
Okay, thank you.

158
00:16:26,210 --> 00:16:29,210
Don't mention it. Hello? What's up?

159
00:16:29,210 --> 00:16:32,241
Hello? What's going on?

160
00:16:32,918 --> 00:16:35,334
Did you see him answering the phone?

161
00:16:35,334 --> 00:16:37,012
Yoo Il Lak has a peculiar style.

162
00:16:37,012 --> 00:16:39,014
He's still like that
even knowing the real Jung Shi Won?

163
00:16:39,014 --> 00:16:41,417
Leave him alone.

164
00:16:41,417 --> 00:16:43,918
He's willing to sacrifice himself
for all the male in the world.

165
00:16:43,918 --> 00:16:45,587
Hey!

166
00:16:53,143 --> 00:16:55,479
I'm so stupid.

167
00:16:59,397 --> 00:17:02,877
I don't want
to suggest a drug treatment to you.

168
00:17:02,877 --> 00:17:05,446
Let's think about other options.

169
00:17:05,446 --> 00:17:09,545
By the way,
do you really want to get it treated?

170
00:17:09,545 --> 00:17:13,682
When I saw you for hypnotherapy,
you seem content with your current state.

171
00:17:14,747 --> 00:17:15,710
It's Yoon Hoo!

172
00:17:15,710 --> 00:17:17,169
- Is it Yoon Hoo?
- Yes.

173
00:17:17,169 --> 00:17:18,960
Is it a group text?

174
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:22,002
A group text is all we get?

175
00:17:22,002 --> 00:17:23,692
What's the attached file?

176
00:17:27,163 --> 00:17:29,710
There are so many pretty noonas here.

177
00:17:29,710 --> 00:17:31,376
I believe everyone is doing well?

178
00:17:31,376 --> 00:17:32,918
I miss you.

179
00:17:32,918 --> 00:17:34,703
Where is he?

180
00:17:37,199 --> 00:17:38,900
It looks like Juilliard, right?

181
00:17:40,356 --> 00:17:42,835
Maybe he won't come to Han Eum anymore.

182
00:17:42,835 --> 00:17:46,127
He wouldn't leave without a word like this.
I'm disappointed.

183
00:17:46,127 --> 00:17:47,751
Pretty noonas?

184
00:17:47,751 --> 00:17:52,387
I'm so jealous. He is really in Heaven.

185
00:18:32,408 --> 00:18:35,960
Yoon Hoo! Thanks for the snack.

186
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:38,867
Thank you! Just tell me anytime, noona.

187
00:18:51,418 --> 00:18:53,169
What brought you here?

188
00:18:53,169 --> 00:18:56,626
You came to visit me, by any chance?

189
00:18:56,626 --> 00:18:59,521
No, it's a coincidence. Not a very happy one.

190
00:19:01,123 --> 00:19:06,495
By the way,
since when was I on your friends' list?

191
00:19:10,738 --> 00:19:13,782
Were you the one
who called on the day of surgery?

192
00:19:13,782 --> 00:19:15,127
What?

193
00:19:15,127 --> 00:19:17,319
"A friend I don't know the name of."

194
00:19:18,079 --> 00:19:19,826
So this is you.

195
00:19:26,671 --> 00:19:30,341
Why do you have to hide about that hand?

196
00:19:31,220 --> 00:19:33,918
You're doing a good job of hiding it, too.

197
00:19:33,918 --> 00:19:36,024
I don't need to go around tell them.

198
00:19:36,632 --> 00:19:37,866
Me too.

199
00:19:39,128 --> 00:19:43,543
I don't want
my friends to look at me and feel despair.

200
00:19:43,543 --> 00:19:45,956
I only want to show them
the bright side of me.

201
00:19:46,969 --> 00:19:50,005
Carrying it alone wasn't that great.

202
00:19:50,940 --> 00:19:52,708
It's up to you since it's your choice.

203
00:19:54,908 --> 00:19:56,809
You're surprisingly nosy.

204
00:19:58,793 --> 00:20:03,064
Still, thank you for stopping me
from performing the duet.

205
00:20:04,752 --> 00:20:07,501
We paid back each other's debt with this.

206
00:20:07,501 --> 00:20:09,692
A clean relationship without debt issues.

207
00:20:09,692 --> 00:20:13,495
I didn't have anything
I owed or wanted from you in the first place.

208
00:20:15,595 --> 00:20:17,129
Bye.

209
00:20:23,895 --> 00:20:25,481
I know.

210
00:20:26,314 --> 00:20:29,196
I didn't want any debt
in a mediocre friendship.

211
00:20:29,985 --> 00:20:31,453
So that's great.

212
00:20:42,413 --> 00:20:45,169
- Orabang!
- Almighty Cha!

213
00:20:45,169 --> 00:20:48,293
- Yoo Jin!
- Yoo Jin!

214
00:20:48,293 --> 00:20:50,835
It's my fault.

215
00:20:50,835 --> 00:20:53,487
Lak, what did I tell you?

216
00:21:24,538 --> 00:21:29,127
Professor, now I added chords
as you told me to,

217
00:21:29,127 --> 00:21:32,043
it feels much more urgent.

218
00:21:32,043 --> 00:21:34,276
Let's go.

219
00:21:44,808 --> 00:21:46,210
Sforzando!

220
00:21:46,210 --> 00:21:50,926
Yes, the big event ended just now.

221
00:21:55,090 --> 00:21:59,001
Of course. After that, 'tempo rubato.'

222
00:21:59,782 --> 00:22:01,937
Shouldn't we go with a free style?

223
00:22:03,202 --> 00:22:05,162
That's a great idea!

224
00:22:05,162 --> 00:22:09,585
Professor, you finally grasped
the essence of gas.

225
00:22:09,585 --> 00:22:12,414
It's nothing.
Should we go back to the beginning?

226
00:22:14,409 --> 00:22:15,910
Go!

227
00:22:21,589 --> 00:22:23,585
It really is a good song.

228
00:22:23,585 --> 00:22:25,418
The structure is great, too.

229
00:22:25,418 --> 00:22:28,210
Professor Ahn, this is indeed
like a treasure.

230
00:22:28,210 --> 00:22:31,033
But what about the ending I helped?

231
00:22:31,033 --> 00:22:33,585
The final stop of the long Fart Song.

232
00:22:33,585 --> 00:22:36,705
The majestic spectacle
that meets with a powerful bowl movement!

233
00:22:38,488 --> 00:22:40,723
Bravo!

234
00:22:43,869 --> 00:22:45,637
Professor.

235
00:22:46,461 --> 00:22:48,162
Good job.

236
00:22:51,928 --> 00:22:53,835
Thank you.

237
00:22:53,835 --> 00:22:57,043
It's been a long time
since I had a fun lesson.

238
00:22:57,043 --> 00:23:00,169
I had forgotten about all this fun
for a while.

239
00:23:00,169 --> 00:23:03,293
Let's work on "Fluffy Fluffy" starting tomorrow.

240
00:23:03,293 --> 00:23:04,169
I'll prepare...

241
00:23:04,169 --> 00:23:06,868
Professor, hold on.

242
00:23:07,847 --> 00:23:10,460
Why? You don't want to?

243
00:23:10,460 --> 00:23:12,440
I heard you prepared it with Professor Ahn.

244
00:23:13,155 --> 00:23:17,751
Professor, until when
will you just play around?

245
00:23:17,751 --> 00:23:20,334
Shouldn't we get ready for the competition?

246
00:23:20,334 --> 00:23:21,043
What?

247
00:23:21,043 --> 00:23:24,719
We should get ready
for the Baek Geon Soo Competition.

248
00:23:25,760 --> 00:23:27,210
I'm requesting lessons

249
00:23:27,210 --> 00:23:30,564
to prepare
for the competition starting tomorrow.

250
00:23:40,302 --> 00:23:41,918
Competition?

251
00:23:41,918 --> 00:23:43,438
Bravo!

252
00:24:06,028 --> 00:24:07,396
Dean.

253
00:24:07,960 --> 00:24:09,397
Yoo Jin!

254
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:12,200
What is it about?

255
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:14,501
I have a really good news.

256
00:24:14,501 --> 00:24:17,751
Oh, you don't like being in the media.

257
00:24:17,751 --> 00:24:22,344
But I'd like you to appear this time
since the conductor is the main focus.

258
00:24:23,676 --> 00:24:26,626
Is it really necessary?

259
00:24:26,626 --> 00:24:27,960
Think about it.

260
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:31,585
It's a chance to let people know

261
00:24:31,585 --> 00:24:33,822
that Rising Star is
the official Han Eum Orchestra.

262
00:24:37,512 --> 00:24:40,169
To the melody of classical music.

263
00:24:40,169 --> 00:24:43,043
I'd like to request

264
00:24:43,043 --> 00:24:46,376
that Rising Star members participate
in the filming.

265
00:24:46,376 --> 00:24:47,793
Dean Song Mi Na.

266
00:24:47,793 --> 00:24:50,710
Oh, filming?

267
00:24:50,710 --> 00:24:52,835
All the TV station cameras
were swarming last time,

268
00:24:52,835 --> 00:24:54,668
and they're coming this week!

269
00:24:54,668 --> 00:24:56,645
We're finally national!

270
00:24:56,645 --> 00:25:00,085
My father would pass out
if he knew I'd be on TV!

271
00:25:00,085 --> 00:25:02,317
He'll be really happy.

272
00:25:03,018 --> 00:25:07,418
Being on TV what's so great
about showing your face on TV?

273
00:25:07,418 --> 00:25:09,763
It'll be great promotion for us.

274
00:25:09,763 --> 00:25:11,426
Then so many people will be there for us.

275
00:25:11,426 --> 00:25:14,696
That's awesome!

276
00:25:14,696 --> 00:25:18,751
This program is known to connect performers
with major label and recording studios.

277
00:25:18,751 --> 00:25:21,877
Son Soo Ji got a contract
through this program, too.

278
00:25:21,877 --> 00:25:23,127
Really?

279
00:25:23,127 --> 00:25:25,877
She got a contract with Lusa
after this program.

280
00:25:25,877 --> 00:25:27,275
Lusa? Really?

281
00:25:27,275 --> 00:25:30,379
Then our soloist albums
will be possible, too.

282
00:25:30,379 --> 00:25:33,882
That's where my idol oboe soloist
had his contract, too.

283
00:25:36,945 --> 00:25:39,418
What if they attack us to get a contract?

284
00:25:39,418 --> 00:25:40,855
It'll be a big success for all of us!

285
00:25:43,160 --> 00:25:44,293
It's my dad!

286
00:25:44,293 --> 00:25:46,494
Me too! Me too!

287
00:25:49,264 --> 00:25:51,210
Sorry.

288
00:25:51,210 --> 00:25:53,935
It would be nice if I could participate.

289
00:25:53,935 --> 00:25:55,570
But I have to go to Europe right away.

290
00:25:57,097 --> 00:25:59,666
You're an idol of classical music,
so you're busy.

291
00:26:00,441 --> 00:26:02,643
You'll get there soon.

292
00:26:03,545 --> 00:26:07,210
"Move aside, idols.
Conductor-idol is coming.

293
00:26:07,210 --> 00:26:11,751
The conductor
who plays the biggest instrument,

294
00:26:11,751 --> 00:26:12,988
an orchestra."

295
00:26:15,204 --> 00:26:17,877
That will be a frame used for you.

296
00:26:17,877 --> 00:26:19,494
That's horrifying.

297
00:26:20,710 --> 00:26:23,532
How long will you stay here?

298
00:26:23,532 --> 00:26:27,268
Do you really plan to stay here
until RS is settled?

299
00:26:28,403 --> 00:26:29,804
I started it.

300
00:26:31,505 --> 00:26:33,626
It's just strange.

301
00:26:33,626 --> 00:26:38,418
There are a lot of instruments in the world
that you want to play.

302
00:26:38,418 --> 00:26:41,585
Don't you want to play those instruments?

303
00:26:41,585 --> 00:26:44,386
The real orchestras in the world.

304
00:26:45,735 --> 00:26:49,972
Are we close enough
to talk about this kind of stuff?

305
00:26:51,334 --> 00:26:53,460
You're being so formal.

306
00:26:53,460 --> 00:26:55,501
Think about it.

307
00:26:55,501 --> 00:26:58,074
A lot of orchestras are interested in you.

308
00:27:00,542 --> 00:27:02,310
Sunbae!

309
00:27:17,349 --> 00:27:21,501
Why are you here?
I heard you went abroad for your concerts.

310
00:27:21,501 --> 00:27:24,460
Looking at you,
I don't want to leave anymore.

311
00:27:24,460 --> 00:27:25,960
Should I just stay here?

312
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:28,938
What? Why?

313
00:27:29,773 --> 00:27:32,709
If you can't see me, will you leave?

314
00:27:33,757 --> 00:27:35,877
I'm going to hide!

315
00:27:35,877 --> 00:27:37,413
I'm hiding!

316
00:27:38,648 --> 00:27:39,983
Why are you so cute?

317
00:27:41,010 --> 00:27:42,745
Do you want to come with me?

318
00:27:44,751 --> 00:27:47,127
No.

319
00:27:47,127 --> 00:27:49,334
Aren't you leaving? You said you were busy.

320
00:27:49,334 --> 00:27:51,427
Why are you on alert?

321
00:27:52,028 --> 00:27:55,431
See you next year. I'll stop by.

322
00:28:02,896 --> 00:28:04,531
Sunbae.

323
00:28:06,506 --> 00:28:11,293
There are a lot of instruments in the world
that you want to play.

324
00:28:11,293 --> 00:28:13,883
Don't you want to play those instruments?

325
00:28:15,426 --> 00:28:17,169
Hey! Seol Nae Il!

326
00:28:17,169 --> 00:28:19,043
Hurry up! We're having a meeting.

327
00:28:19,043 --> 00:28:21,491
Sunbae, let's hurry.

328
00:28:21,491 --> 00:28:24,093
The real orchestras in the world.

329
00:28:28,994 --> 00:28:32,376
Let's go with Trumpet Concerto by Haydn.
I can do it.

330
00:28:32,376 --> 00:28:35,638
No, we should go with a violin concerto.

331
00:28:38,305 --> 00:28:41,251
What about a contrabass concerto?

332
00:28:41,251 --> 00:28:43,210
Let's just go with a oboe concerto.

333
00:28:43,210 --> 00:28:45,127
I can do it, too.

334
00:28:45,127 --> 00:28:47,334
There is a timpani concerto, too.

335
00:28:47,334 --> 00:28:50,453
You're getting too greedy for the TV program.

336
00:28:50,453 --> 00:28:53,210
A performance as a soloist at the S level?

337
00:28:53,210 --> 00:28:57,794
It will just be a big humiliation
at the concert and on the program.

338
00:29:01,620 --> 00:29:04,710
Who's S and who is A? We're all Rising Star.

339
00:29:04,710 --> 00:29:07,403
Yes, all of us are good now.

340
00:29:08,170 --> 00:29:12,374
That's only when you piggyback on our sound.

341
00:29:13,201 --> 00:29:14,918
- What?
- That's all you can say?

342
00:29:14,918 --> 00:29:16,413
You're too mean.

343
00:29:16,413 --> 00:29:18,915
Did I say something wrong?

344
00:29:24,770 --> 00:29:26,638
That's enough.

345
00:29:27,964 --> 00:29:29,766
Let's have the meeting at another time.

346
00:29:41,534 --> 00:29:43,460
Sunbae!

347
00:29:43,460 --> 00:29:47,110
Sunbae, you have such charisma!
You ended it in one swing.

348
00:29:47,110 --> 00:29:50,347
A and S seemed to get along,
but there they go again.

349
00:29:50,347 --> 00:29:52,960
They'll stop soon. Don't worry about it.

350
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:55,501
I think it'll be pretty bad this time.

351
00:29:55,501 --> 00:29:58,751
Everyone has high expectations
for the TV program.

352
00:29:58,751 --> 00:30:02,091
I guess their future depends on it.

353
00:30:06,896 --> 00:30:07,835
What?

354
00:30:07,835 --> 00:30:11,668
You're like a dad worried about his children.

355
00:30:11,668 --> 00:30:13,403
Dad?

356
00:30:14,067 --> 00:30:17,460
And I'm a mom.

357
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:20,343
The mom who is not worried
about the children,

358
00:30:20,343 --> 00:30:21,866
but who is preparing for a competition.

359
00:30:21,866 --> 00:30:25,148
Staying as the mascot is...

360
00:30:25,148 --> 00:30:26,585
Competition?

361
00:30:26,585 --> 00:30:28,251
You decided to go for the competition??

362
00:30:28,251 --> 00:30:30,753
Yes. Pat me on the back.

363
00:30:32,249 --> 00:30:33,460
Isn't it too soon?

364
00:30:33,460 --> 00:30:36,659
Just think about what you'll get me
when I win the competition.

365
00:30:37,880 --> 00:30:39,793
Seol Nae Il is getting ahead
of herself again.

366
00:30:39,793 --> 00:30:41,898
It's not that easy.

367
00:30:42,595 --> 00:30:45,460
S kids don't know their place.

368
00:30:45,460 --> 00:30:48,071
Who made the RS concert a success?

369
00:30:48,071 --> 00:30:50,585
There isn't anyone good enough
to be a soloist over there.

370
00:30:50,585 --> 00:30:52,501
They are just being greedy.

371
00:30:52,501 --> 00:30:55,478
We performed with Son Soo Ji.

372
00:30:55,478 --> 00:30:57,847
A soloist among those losers?

373
00:30:58,488 --> 00:31:01,418
Our level is dropping.

374
00:31:01,418 --> 00:31:04,354
Besides, it's filming for a TV program.

375
00:31:04,354 --> 00:31:08,358
It is a good chance
to get your name out there as a soloist.

376
00:31:08,358 --> 00:31:10,093
You can't pick that one.

377
00:31:20,967 --> 00:31:23,460
A kids are talking behind our back.

378
00:31:23,460 --> 00:31:26,127
- These punks...
- We don't care about A anymore.

379
00:31:26,127 --> 00:31:29,345
They keep looking down on us.

380
00:31:29,345 --> 00:31:32,949
If a soloist is picked from one of us,
they'd rather leave.

381
00:31:34,584 --> 00:31:36,152
What the heck is this?

382
00:31:36,152 --> 00:31:38,655
They lost rationality
over the thought of soloist.

383
00:31:38,655 --> 00:31:40,456
Nerds!

384
00:31:41,833 --> 00:31:43,376
Should we break it off?

385
00:31:43,376 --> 00:31:45,293
Should we?

386
00:31:45,293 --> 00:31:47,096
Seriously...

387
00:31:48,938 --> 00:31:51,173
That shouldn't happen.

388
00:32:17,607 --> 00:32:21,293
Stop, everyone.
Let's decide on the soloist first.

389
00:32:21,293 --> 00:32:24,100
That's right.
Don't be stubborn about your own parts.

390
00:32:24,100 --> 00:32:25,626
Let's consider the skills first.

391
00:32:25,626 --> 00:32:28,127
That's of course us.

392
00:32:28,127 --> 00:32:31,340
The visual part is also important
since it'll be on TV.

393
00:32:34,410 --> 00:32:37,418
This face will work on TV.

394
00:32:37,418 --> 00:32:39,382
Yes, that's right.

395
00:32:40,215 --> 00:32:43,384
If you go on TV with those faces,
you'll gain a million anti-fans in no time.

396
00:32:43,969 --> 00:32:45,670
S is for the visual.

397
00:32:47,050 --> 00:32:49,960
Stop it! I don't even want to be soloist.

398
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:51,835
Yes, let's at least respect each other.

399
00:32:51,835 --> 00:32:53,418
Forget it.

400
00:32:53,418 --> 00:32:55,565
I don't even like sharing the practice room
with them.

401
00:32:55,565 --> 00:32:58,101
If you don't like it, then leave!

402
00:32:58,101 --> 00:32:59,769
That's right.

403
00:33:04,741 --> 00:33:09,376
"We popped champagne too early"?
What do you mean, Franz?

404
00:33:09,376 --> 00:33:12,585
About the orchestra members.

405
00:33:12,585 --> 00:33:18,169
It's not necessarily good
that we got the official approval.

406
00:33:18,169 --> 00:33:20,423
We needed the approval to get support.

407
00:33:20,423 --> 00:33:21,793
Don't worry.

408
00:33:21,793 --> 00:33:25,251
They even had a taste of fame
from the RS concert.

409
00:33:25,251 --> 00:33:27,830
They'll do a good job on their own now.

410
00:33:29,039 --> 00:33:32,210
If a baby who just started taking steps
tries to run,

411
00:33:32,210 --> 00:33:34,751
of course he will fall.

412
00:33:34,751 --> 00:33:38,875
If he is fascinated by small successes,
he misses obvious things.

413
00:33:40,343 --> 00:33:45,915
I believe this is the most dangerous time.

414
00:33:48,700 --> 00:33:51,502
What do you mean?
Where are you now, Dan Ya?

415
00:33:52,422 --> 00:33:53,418
- Lak!
- Dan Ya!

416
00:33:53,418 --> 00:33:54,501
What do I do?

417
00:33:54,501 --> 00:33:56,425
Let's go.

418
00:34:00,797 --> 00:34:02,460
Mini Min Hee! Hurry!

419
00:34:02,460 --> 00:34:05,368
- Wait for me, Lak!
- Wait for me!

420
00:34:07,136 --> 00:34:09,805
Hurry! Hurry!

421
00:34:10,607 --> 00:34:12,942
- Open the door!
- Open the door!

422
00:34:13,932 --> 00:34:15,376
- They locked it.
- Is it locked?

423
00:34:15,376 --> 00:34:18,334
- Yes it is.
- Hey, open the door!

424
00:34:18,334 --> 00:34:20,501
- What is it?
- What's going on?

425
00:34:20,501 --> 00:34:22,626
They locked the door!

426
00:34:22,626 --> 00:34:25,621
They locked the door? You're not kids.

427
00:34:26,085 --> 00:34:29,085
Hey, let's talk it out.

428
00:34:29,085 --> 00:34:31,661
Weren't you the one
who punched in the first place?

429
00:34:31,661 --> 00:34:34,793
- I don't want to share the practice room.
- Me neither.

430
00:34:34,793 --> 00:34:35,751
Right?

431
00:34:35,751 --> 00:34:37,574
Punch?

432
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:41,035
He was really on my nerve,
so just a little...

433
00:34:43,639 --> 00:34:45,341
It was really a light one though.

434
00:34:45,341 --> 00:34:47,944
Yes, I'm a witness.

435
00:34:49,261 --> 00:34:50,862
A light one?

436
00:34:52,869 --> 00:34:55,538
Let's block them too.

437
00:34:56,101 --> 00:34:58,436
Let's do that!

438
00:35:07,497 --> 00:35:08,998
Push! Push!

439
00:35:11,867 --> 00:35:18,210
One, two! One, two!

440
00:35:18,210 --> 00:35:23,877
One, two! One, two!

441
00:35:23,877 --> 00:35:28,749
One, two! One, two!

442
00:35:41,730 --> 00:35:43,485
Are you okay?

443
00:36:08,418 --> 00:36:10,501
We have two solutions.

444
00:36:10,501 --> 00:36:12,355
Choose one of the them.

445
00:36:15,258 --> 00:36:19,429
First, the cause of this trouble is soloist.

446
00:36:20,898 --> 00:36:22,960
We'll go with music without a soloist.

447
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:25,602
What are you saying? That's nonsense.

448
00:36:25,602 --> 00:36:28,085
- No way.
- That's not right.

449
00:36:28,085 --> 00:36:30,073
- Yeah.
- Second...

450
00:36:32,904 --> 00:36:34,866
an open audition.

451
00:36:34,877 --> 00:36:39,048
After that, pick your own soloist by voting.

452
00:36:41,985 --> 00:36:46,155
There are about equal numbers of A and S,
so it won't be a problem.

453
00:36:46,837 --> 00:36:51,775
Write down the names
who are good as soloists from the other team.

454
00:36:52,281 --> 00:36:55,877
Then we write down the names from A members.

455
00:36:55,877 --> 00:36:58,301
And we write the S loser...

456
00:37:02,905 --> 00:37:04,210
We write one of their names?

457
00:37:04,210 --> 00:37:05,793
We can't do that!

458
00:37:05,793 --> 00:37:08,344
We can't play with those people!

459
00:37:08,344 --> 00:37:10,947
If you don't want to...

460
00:37:12,849 --> 00:37:15,584
we'll go with music without a soloist.

461
00:37:18,988 --> 00:37:21,418
I have the right to choose the music.

462
00:37:21,418 --> 00:37:23,520
If you don't like it, do whatever you want.

463
00:37:45,334 --> 00:37:47,903
Don't you want to play those instruments?

464
00:37:48,510 --> 00:37:50,945
The real orchestras in the world.

465
00:38:03,319 --> 00:38:05,020
You picked Haydn?

466
00:38:06,877 --> 00:38:08,679
Have you played it before?

467
00:38:08,679 --> 00:38:13,784
No, but I was attracted to it
from the homework.

468
00:38:14,837 --> 00:38:16,501
How should I say it?

469
00:38:16,501 --> 00:38:19,793
It's something like a desire
to date someone with a different style

470
00:38:19,793 --> 00:38:22,210
than my usual type?

471
00:38:22,210 --> 00:38:24,668
Date someone within your type.

472
00:38:24,668 --> 00:38:25,793
We don't even have time,

473
00:38:25,793 --> 00:38:28,334
so why do you want
to pretend to act like a playgirl?

474
00:38:28,334 --> 00:38:31,002
No, I want to play this one.

475
00:38:31,002 --> 00:38:34,018
I don't know much about other music anyway.

476
00:38:34,661 --> 00:38:37,543
And I stayed up all night to practice it.

477
00:38:37,543 --> 00:38:39,710
You practiced it?

478
00:38:39,710 --> 00:38:41,426
Okay, then try it.

479
00:39:32,744 --> 00:39:34,646
Look at the score!

480
00:39:34,646 --> 00:39:36,835
Don't get drunk in your own emotions

481
00:39:36,835 --> 00:39:38,550
and make whatever sound you want!

482
00:39:38,550 --> 00:39:40,501
You should cut that off!

483
00:39:40,501 --> 00:39:43,388
Transfer the score onto the piano exactly!

484
00:39:48,159 --> 00:39:49,751
If you go with your feeling
in the preliminary round,

485
00:39:49,751 --> 00:39:51,596
you will be eliminated.

486
00:40:25,330 --> 00:40:29,334
Are you saying
that there is a problem with Seol Nae Il?

487
00:40:29,334 --> 00:40:31,970
All geniuses have their own timing.

488
00:40:32,790 --> 00:40:37,394
If they don't know what they are born with
and don't have any opportunities

489
00:40:38,255 --> 00:40:40,457
they have no choice
but to live an ordinary life.

490
00:40:42,046 --> 00:40:43,681
What do you mean?

491
00:40:44,909 --> 00:40:49,680
I feel like I'm forcing her into a box.

492
00:40:51,119 --> 00:40:51,918
Pardon?

493
00:40:51,918 --> 00:40:56,793
Seol Nae Il doesn't like playing it
the way it's in the score.

494
00:40:56,793 --> 00:41:00,631
She can't forget
how she used to follow her feeling.

495
00:41:01,716 --> 00:41:03,251
It may work in the final round,

496
00:41:03,251 --> 00:41:05,820
but she won't be accepted
in the preliminary round.

497
00:41:07,098 --> 00:41:10,668
If she can't pass the preliminary round,
what's the use of the final round?

498
00:41:12,577 --> 00:41:17,882
I'm worried
that I discovered Seol Nae Il too late.

499
00:41:35,834 --> 00:41:37,802
Come to my house.

500
00:41:42,835 --> 00:41:44,570
What are these?

501
00:41:44,570 --> 00:41:47,085
Things you need to do after your practice.

502
00:41:47,085 --> 00:41:49,241
Make sure to wear the gloves.

503
00:41:49,241 --> 00:41:52,002
It'll help you
if you soak your hands in warm water

504
00:41:52,002 --> 00:41:53,501
before the practice.

505
00:41:53,501 --> 00:41:55,668
Don't use your hands except for the piano.

506
00:41:55,668 --> 00:41:58,016
No sewing machine.

507
00:41:58,817 --> 00:42:01,219
You'll hurt your hands
trying to sew your own stage costume.

508
00:42:02,822 --> 00:42:07,125
But, Sunbae, you heard from Professor Do.

509
00:42:08,980 --> 00:42:12,043
I'm not saying
that I'm not entering the competition.

510
00:42:12,043 --> 00:42:14,293
I just need to practice for a few more days.

511
00:42:14,293 --> 00:42:17,869
I'm not used to following the score yet.

512
00:42:24,242 --> 00:42:28,501
It's the performance completely fitted
for the judges' taste.

513
00:42:29,721 --> 00:42:31,559
Can you memorize it?

514
00:42:32,931 --> 00:42:36,210
Professor Do doesn't know you that well yet.

515
00:42:37,222 --> 00:42:40,692
He only saw a part of your talent
and now he's in despair.

516
00:42:41,399 --> 00:42:43,668
Of course he wouldn't know that it's faster

517
00:42:44,676 --> 00:42:46,611
for you to hear the music than read it.

518
00:42:49,220 --> 00:42:53,793
Follow the frame just for a while.

519
00:42:53,793 --> 00:42:56,085
Once the world gets to know you,

520
00:42:56,085 --> 00:42:58,577
then play however you want.

521
00:43:04,616 --> 00:43:06,918
You played this, right?

522
00:43:08,641 --> 00:43:10,668
I had free time.

523
00:43:10,668 --> 00:43:13,835
You would have been be busy
preparing for the orchestra music.

524
00:43:13,835 --> 00:43:16,271
I have free time in between.

525
00:43:16,271 --> 00:43:18,940
Oh, my God.

526
00:43:32,865 --> 00:43:35,251
Imagine that you're dating Haydn.

527
00:43:35,251 --> 00:43:39,193
Then you'll want to hit each note perfectly.

528
00:43:46,626 --> 00:43:49,131
It's your own style again!

529
00:43:49,131 --> 00:43:51,668
The essence of music is enjoyment?

530
00:43:51,668 --> 00:43:54,543
You can only enjoy as much as you know.

531
00:43:54,543 --> 00:43:57,770
Don't play by your feeling. Follow the score.

532
00:43:58,571 --> 00:44:01,607
It's more difficult
to follow the standard way.

533
00:45:26,022 --> 00:45:27,623
Isn't that Yoon Hoo?

534
00:45:28,877 --> 00:45:30,645
Lee Yoon Hoo!

535
00:45:31,945 --> 00:45:34,080
- Lee Yoon Hoo!
- It's you!

536
00:45:35,404 --> 00:45:37,668
- Where have you been?
- Il Lak!

537
00:45:37,668 --> 00:45:40,169
When did you come back to Korea?

538
00:45:40,169 --> 00:45:42,877
Are you just stopping by?
Just to say goodbye and leave?

539
00:45:42,877 --> 00:45:44,751
No way.

540
00:45:44,751 --> 00:45:46,762
Mini Min Hee, it's been a while.

541
00:45:46,762 --> 00:45:48,730
You're still cute.

542
00:45:50,365 --> 00:45:52,085
And you're still the same.

543
00:45:52,085 --> 00:45:54,418
What happened?
You disappeared without a word.

544
00:45:54,418 --> 00:45:56,653
Yes, you canceled the duet and disappeared.

545
00:45:56,653 --> 00:45:57,710
And Nae Il didn't say anything.

546
00:45:57,710 --> 00:46:00,557
The dean had a hard time handling it.

547
00:46:00,557 --> 00:46:04,695
My mom also said
she was busy submitting statements.

548
00:46:06,104 --> 00:46:08,773
What happened? Did you get hurt?

549
00:46:10,346 --> 00:46:12,736
It's a light fracture.

550
00:46:12,736 --> 00:46:15,751
I'm just being careful. It's no big deal.

551
00:46:15,751 --> 00:46:18,275
It must hurt.

552
00:46:18,275 --> 00:46:21,668
Are you okay? Still, it looks bad.

553
00:46:21,668 --> 00:46:25,048
Are you all worried about me?

554
00:46:26,708 --> 00:46:28,743
That makes me happy.

555
00:46:29,651 --> 00:46:33,835
By the way, is My Nae Il busy preparing
for the competition?

556
00:46:33,835 --> 00:46:36,760
- Why isn't she around?
- Yes, she's busy...

557
00:46:40,190 --> 00:46:42,492
"My Nae Il"?

558
00:46:54,608 --> 00:46:56,293
Yoon Hoo!

559
00:46:56,293 --> 00:46:58,751
You got prettier, Nae Il.

560
00:46:58,751 --> 00:47:00,450
Didn't you miss me?

561
00:47:01,034 --> 00:47:04,271
I did miss you.

562
00:47:05,210 --> 00:47:09,214
Still, you shouldn't do this.
I have a boyfriend.

563
00:47:09,214 --> 00:47:11,835
I already know that.

564
00:47:11,835 --> 00:47:15,386
By the way, you look a little different.

565
00:47:16,867 --> 00:47:20,325
I heard people change when they get sick.

566
00:47:20,325 --> 00:47:22,393
Are you really sick?

567
00:47:26,598 --> 00:47:29,460
What happened? You said it was no big deal.

568
00:47:29,460 --> 00:47:33,504
To be honest, I was really in pain then.

569
00:47:37,460 --> 00:47:38,960
I'm joking.

570
00:47:38,960 --> 00:47:40,626
It wasn't anything serious then.

571
00:47:40,626 --> 00:47:42,626
I got a slight injury after that.

572
00:47:42,626 --> 00:47:44,801
I'm just being careful, so I got a cast.

573
00:47:50,005 --> 00:47:52,541
I'm happy that Nae Il is worried about me.

574
00:47:53,970 --> 00:47:56,238
Now I feel like I'm back.

575
00:47:57,799 --> 00:48:00,968
You've changed a lot Yoon Hoo...

576
00:48:03,460 --> 00:48:12,584
[Open Audition]

577
00:49:07,877 --> 00:49:10,751
Is she playing the viola or seducing a man?

578
00:49:10,751 --> 00:49:13,149
Why? I like it.

579
00:50:06,936 --> 00:50:08,668
Yoo Il Lak is pretty good.

580
00:50:08,668 --> 00:50:11,543
But he chose Tchaikovsky

581
00:50:11,543 --> 00:50:13,976
knowing that Shi Won picked
that music, right?

582
00:50:14,876 --> 00:50:17,846
I guess Yoo Il Lak truly isn't interested
in being a soloist.

583
00:50:52,012 --> 00:50:56,686
Yoo Il Lak, did you choose that music
knowing that Si Won picked the same one?

584
00:50:57,460 --> 00:50:59,918
That way, we'll be compared.
My bandmaster is really good.

585
00:50:59,918 --> 00:51:02,169
- You're such an idiot.
- Such an idiot.

586
00:51:02,169 --> 00:51:06,202
We had a concert with Son Soo Ji.
There must be a lot of interest.

587
00:51:06,202 --> 00:51:09,439
It should be Shi Won
with her talented skill as a RS soloist.

588
00:51:09,439 --> 00:51:13,976
It's true, but I just can't stand A members.

589
00:51:27,210 --> 00:51:29,668
Let's pick the soloist next week.

590
00:51:29,668 --> 00:51:31,877
Everyone will need time to think.

591
00:51:31,877 --> 00:51:33,783
We've roughly made the decision on the music.

592
00:51:34,835 --> 00:51:37,538
With a common sense,
the result will be obvious.

593
00:51:37,538 --> 00:51:40,607
Yes, the result will be obvious.

594
00:51:44,418 --> 00:51:47,697
- It's a bit hot here.
- Is it?

595
00:51:52,888 --> 00:51:54,585
They didn't say anything, did they?

596
00:51:55,626 --> 00:51:57,791
Of course not!

597
00:51:57,791 --> 00:52:00,210
All of us know our own skill level.

598
00:52:00,210 --> 00:52:03,463
If we have a fair vote, it'll be the end.
All the issues will be resolved.

599
00:52:12,460 --> 00:52:16,597
At this rate, which name would
the S members write down?

600
00:52:16,597 --> 00:52:17,835
Who knows.

601
00:52:17,835 --> 00:52:19,900
It'll be Shi Won following common sense,

602
00:52:20,541 --> 00:52:22,743
but would S members pick Shi Won?

603
00:52:23,626 --> 00:52:28,127
Then we can't give our votes
to one person easily.

604
00:52:28,127 --> 00:52:29,376
What do you plan to do?

605
00:52:29,376 --> 00:52:31,931
Shi Won is really good.

606
00:52:31,931 --> 00:52:36,602
If all the votes go to her,
A will have a soloist.

607
00:52:36,602 --> 00:52:39,169
- But that can't happen.
- Of course not.

608
00:52:39,169 --> 00:52:43,509
I'd miss the filming
rather than handing over a soloist to A.

609
00:52:44,753 --> 00:52:47,822
Then what do we do now?

610
00:52:54,043 --> 00:52:56,501
Let's decide on someone who can't do well

611
00:52:56,501 --> 00:53:00,838
or someone who'll give up on his own.

612
00:53:02,646 --> 00:53:06,550
You don't want a soloist
from A members, do you?

613
00:53:08,062 --> 00:53:10,631
Then there is only one way.

614
00:53:33,965 --> 00:53:35,710
Hey.

615
00:53:35,710 --> 00:53:38,501
We didn't do anything wrong,
so why are we shooting a spy movie?

616
00:53:38,501 --> 00:53:39,960
You never know.

617
00:53:39,960 --> 00:53:41,460
Everyone's so sensitive right now.

618
00:53:41,460 --> 00:53:43,835
If we told them
that we were discussing together.

619
00:53:43,835 --> 00:53:46,161
They'd call us traitors.

620
00:53:48,143 --> 00:53:49,751
I thought only good things were happening,

621
00:53:49,751 --> 00:53:51,646
but what's this lightening on a clear sky?

622
00:53:52,626 --> 00:53:54,585
What do we do now?

623
00:53:54,585 --> 00:53:57,031
That's why we should unite...

624
00:54:00,585 --> 00:54:01,928
What?

625
00:54:02,626 --> 00:54:04,761
- The smell.
- Huh?

626
00:54:09,946 --> 00:54:14,083
Do I smell?
I brushed my teeth and I washed up.

627
00:54:16,206 --> 00:54:18,374
Your hair smells nice.

628
00:54:19,543 --> 00:54:22,146
I didn't wash my hair for you.

629
00:54:22,146 --> 00:54:25,877
Are you coming on to me right now?

630
00:54:25,877 --> 00:54:27,718
What's with that pickup line?

631
00:54:27,718 --> 00:54:29,626
What pickup line?

632
00:54:29,626 --> 00:54:31,251
It's not like that.

633
00:54:31,251 --> 00:54:34,293
It's a bad habit to flirt with any girl.

634
00:54:34,293 --> 00:54:36,860
I don't flirt with any girl. It's just you!

635
00:54:47,104 --> 00:54:50,441
Because I like you,
that's why I'm flirting with you.

636
00:55:54,109 --> 00:55:56,334
She's about this tall.

637
00:55:56,334 --> 00:55:57,746
Or is she shorter?

638
00:55:58,802 --> 00:56:01,171
Her body is about this big.

639
00:56:01,979 --> 00:56:03,881
What's her size?

640
00:56:08,535 --> 00:56:10,321
Is that the dress?

641
00:56:10,321 --> 00:56:13,085
The dress that Nae Il will wear
to the competition.

642
00:56:13,085 --> 00:56:16,668
No, not yet.
I'm not sure if Nae Il will like...

643
00:56:16,668 --> 00:56:19,997
So it's the type of dress
that Nae Il might like.

644
00:56:26,847 --> 00:56:28,334
Hey! Hey!

645
00:56:28,334 --> 00:56:31,710
I'll get this dress.
I'll come back for a fitting.

646
00:56:31,710 --> 00:56:33,585
I picked this dress first.

647
00:56:33,585 --> 00:56:35,145
I said I would buy it first.

648
00:56:35,145 --> 00:56:37,877
You saw that I picked it first.
You saw me there from earlier.

649
00:56:37,877 --> 00:56:39,626
The one who says first has the priority.

650
00:56:39,626 --> 00:56:41,668
Don't you think you went too far
by snatching the one I picked?

651
00:56:41,668 --> 00:56:42,960
Your hesitation is the problem.

652
00:56:42,960 --> 00:56:44,788
Snatching is not a problem?

653
00:56:45,935 --> 00:56:47,835
Then, you can have it.

654
00:56:47,835 --> 00:56:49,710
I can have that dress custom-made, right?

655
00:56:49,710 --> 00:56:51,169
Of course.

656
00:56:51,169 --> 00:56:53,330
I've been trying to say that.

657
00:56:55,025 --> 00:56:57,828
No, I'll give it to him this time.

658
00:56:58,632 --> 00:57:00,801
Continue to stay alarmed.

659
00:57:07,303 --> 00:57:11,240
That butter boy,
why do I feel like he got stronger?

660
00:57:12,736 --> 00:57:14,570
Come out to the door.

661
00:57:22,726 --> 00:57:24,728
Sunbae, what's up...

662
00:57:31,835 --> 00:57:34,604
I saw something pass by just now.

663
00:57:38,334 --> 00:57:40,169
It's a dress!

664
00:57:40,169 --> 00:57:43,973
Sunbae, this is mine?
This is for my competition?

665
00:57:43,973 --> 00:57:45,467
Then would that be mine?

666
00:57:45,467 --> 00:57:47,410
My goodness!

667
00:57:49,683 --> 00:57:52,552
Shopping is tough.

668
00:57:56,420 --> 00:58:00,668
So you made up your mind?

669
00:58:00,668 --> 00:58:03,918
Yes. There is nothing to decide.

670
00:58:03,918 --> 00:58:06,796
I'm transferring
to von Stresemann's conducting major.

671
00:58:07,872 --> 00:58:12,002
I didn't think you'd come to Han Eum.

672
00:58:12,002 --> 00:58:13,793
I'm a bit surprised.

673
00:58:13,793 --> 00:58:16,172
I'll keep surprising you more.

674
00:58:16,172 --> 00:58:17,540
I look forward to it.

675
00:58:20,961 --> 00:58:22,793
I'll get going now.

676
00:58:22,793 --> 00:58:24,947
It's Nae Il's preliminary round today.

677
00:58:26,182 --> 00:58:29,626
I heard Nae Il was entering the competition.
Is it today?

678
00:58:29,626 --> 00:58:35,169
That's why Cha Yoo Jin ignored my call
and left.

679
00:58:35,169 --> 00:58:39,528
I'm late, too.
I might miss my Nae Il's preliminary round.

680
00:58:40,417 --> 00:58:41,951
Off you go.

681
00:58:48,063 --> 00:58:49,798
"My Nae Il"?

682
00:59:04,253 --> 00:59:06,835
Professor, isn't this pretty?

683
00:59:06,835 --> 00:59:10,169
Yoo Jin got me this dress as a gift.

684
00:59:10,169 --> 00:59:12,002
Bravo!

685
00:59:12,002 --> 00:59:14,530
You're talking about the dress now?
Aren't you nervous?

686
00:59:15,418 --> 00:59:16,668
Remember this.

687
00:59:16,668 --> 00:59:18,710
Do not get excited.

688
00:59:18,710 --> 00:59:20,656
Don't follow your feeling.

689
00:59:20,656 --> 00:59:22,918
You have to follow the score.

690
00:59:22,918 --> 00:59:23,835
Yes.

691
00:59:23,835 --> 00:59:27,127
Just follow the score. Follow the standard.

692
00:59:27,127 --> 00:59:29,832
That's how Haydn becomes Haydn!

693
00:59:30,864 --> 00:59:33,537
Participant No. 25, please be ready.

694
00:59:34,043 --> 00:59:35,604
Yes.

695
00:59:36,698 --> 00:59:38,966
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

696
00:59:49,428 --> 00:59:51,497
Why am I so nervous?

697
01:00:32,509 --> 01:00:34,127
It's a rare occasion!

698
01:00:34,127 --> 01:00:36,532
For you to come to the preliminary round.

699
01:00:36,532 --> 01:00:38,918
Yes, I was asked by someone.

700
01:00:38,918 --> 01:00:44,006
Whoever it is, he must be a big shot
to ask you to come here.

701
01:00:46,308 --> 01:00:50,127
That student's name is Seol Nae Il, right?

702
01:00:50,127 --> 01:00:52,251
Do you know her?

703
01:00:52,251 --> 01:00:55,043
Yes, I know her well.

704
01:00:55,043 --> 01:00:58,987
She ran out of my master class
on the first day.

705
01:01:01,208 --> 01:01:03,743
- Really?
- I see.

706
01:02:37,884 --> 01:02:40,501
Yes, just like that.

707
01:02:40,501 --> 01:02:42,424
You're doing well.

708
01:02:43,056 --> 01:02:45,460
Show the world now...

709
01:02:45,460 --> 01:02:46,962
the pianist...

710
01:02:49,024 --> 01:02:50,592
Seol Nae Il.
